<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-CEEE2F7B-03B7-4C24-8E63-5740A244ECAA" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-CEEE2F7B-03B7-4C24-8E63-5740A244ECAA" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">5936 Imaging device position variation</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-508AAFC7-1920-4D7C-81C5-C5EE4DBEA7DD"><p class="- topic/p ">During the determination of the location of the printheads relative to each other a deviation is found which points towards one or more printheads not positioned properly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In more mathematical terms: The X-positions of the printheads as function of their Y-position differ too much from a straight line. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-ABD60635-9D5B-4958-9509-A697535713A8" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print</u> 
</p><table id="GUID-B9AD1063-ED98-4A11-BE04-959A9CE70277" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="3.72*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">CMxx 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-333B1D63-D631-40FE-9AD4-521D87BBD8AF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9DC62373-174B-4129-9770-80317342E154-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9DC62373-174B-4129-9770-80317342E154-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "><u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step 
</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration step: “NozzleJetVar” which is part of one the following calibration sequences 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Carriage calibration 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Printhead calibration 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle Optimalisation 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Calibrations via SDS 21-6-003 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-353299A1-7865-4BD2-9517-7E978CA3B46F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Analyse/Repair</b></title><p class="- topic/p ">To determine the cause of this warning a Service engineer needs to be present at the engine. 
</p><table id="GUID-DFEF32AD-948A-4B08-B1FE-A45E4FD4F684" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="13.55*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Start 
<xref href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> and select "Carriage Y-calibration" 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Load smooth, white and opaque media (eg: Service media) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Start 
<xref href="GUID-B828E436-A124-4809-981E-2DBE1E09A388.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In case the calibration fails and raises this warning go to the tab “ImageDeviceXPos”. 
</p><fig id="GUID-86F10C79-4A66-4D9E-9924-E5FF4598002F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7BB50587-DCBA-41DB-B012-EB73BC4AEC87-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7BB50587-DCBA-41DB-B012-EB73BC4AEC87-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> A value exceeding 40 µm indicates a mispositioned printhead (In the example given ID1 AND ID3) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the position of the indicated printheads 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the printheads position holes are clean and free of dirt 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-7D8F8F2F-BEE0-4655-A487-8C7317E6E16F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Not applicable 
</p></section><section id="GUID-754A33F6-4348-49E9-8EA2-9365D09E5815" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">During the determination of the rotation of the matrix-plate around the Z-axis (Rz) a linear trend is calculated. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case there is a large deviation on the calculated trend-line this warning is raised. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As only the deviation is determined by the algorithm, this algorithm is unable to determine the source of the deviation. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases the deviation is caused by one or more printheads which are not positioned correctly. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-480B4E14-7AB9-4230-BBE2-97A999EC3E19.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
